Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.index.schema

Class Type

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.index.schema.Type
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractArrayType, BooleanType, DateType, DurationType, GeometryType, LocalDateTimeType, LocalTimeType, NumberType, TextType, ZonedDateTimeType, ZonedTimeType
    abstract class Type
extends Object
    All functionality for reading, writing, comparing, calculating size etc a specific value type in a native index. This is not an enum mostly because of arrays having a shared subclass with lots of shared functionality applicable to all array types. The type classes are state-less singletons and operate on state in GenericKey which is passed in as argument to the methods.

    Looking solely at GenericKey is has a bunch of state with no specific meaning, but they get meaning when looking at them through a Type, where e.g. the fields `long0` and `long1` means perhaps string length of a string or the integer value for a number type.

      • readValue

        abstract boolean readValue​(PageCursor cursor,
                           int size,
                           GenericKey into)
        Deserializes key state from cursor into state.
        Parameters:
        cursor - PageCursor initialized at correct offset to read from.
        size - total number of remaining bytes for this key state.
        into - GenericKey to deserialize the key state into.
        Returns:
        whether or not this was a sane read. Returning false should mean that it was simply a bad read, and that the next read in this shouldRetry loop will get a good read. This will signal that it's not worth it to read any further for this key and that the cursor have been told about this error, via PageCursor.setCursorException(String). Otherwise, for a successful read, returns true.
